{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review accessibility of hospital parking and set minimum space width",
        "additional_details": "There are around 20 disabled spaces at my local hospital, and not a single parent and child space. It should be mandatory for hospitals to make spaces wider to assist. It would help a lot of people out.",
        "background": "Set size requirements for hospital parking spaces. Many people who visit hospitals may be disabled or have children. Yet the car parking spaces seem in some cases to be even smaller than those at supermarkets? How does this make sense? We struggle getting out of cars without dinking the next car.",
